hub_genes_all = {}

for g, wgcna in results.items():
    print(f" Extracting hub genes from cluster {g}...")

    # moduleMembership: kMEDataFrame
    mm_df = wgcna.moduleMembership.copy()
    if 'module' not in mm_df.columns:
        print(f" No 'module' column found in cluster {g}. Skipping.")
        continue

    hub_genes_cluster = {}

    for module in mm_df['module'].unique():
        module_genes = mm_df[mm_df['module'] == module]

        # kMEkME-M1
        kme_cols = [col for col in module_genes.columns if col.startswith('kME')]

        if not kme_cols:
            print(f" No kME columns found in cluster {g}, module {module}")
            continue

        kme_col = kme_cols[0]  # 1

        # : kME > 0.8
        hub_genes = module_genes[module_genes[kme_col] > 0.8]
        hub_genes_sorted = hub_genes.sort_values(by=kme_col, ascending=False)

        hub_genes_cluster[module] = hub_genes_sorted

        # 
        output_path = f"./wgcna_{g}/hub_genes_module_{module}.csv"
        hub_genes_sorted.to_csv(output_path)
        print(f" Saved hub genes for module {module} in cluster {g}  {output_path}")

    hub_genes_all[g] = hub_genes_cluster

from sklearn.feature_selection import VarianceThreshold

def top_variable_genes(df, top_n=5000):
    variances = df.var(axis=0)
    top_genes = variances.sort_values(ascending=False).head(top_n).index
    return df[top_genes]

hub_genes_all = {}


for g, wgcna in results.items():
    print(f" Processing cluster {g} for hub genes...")

    try:
        wgcna.CalculateSignedKME()
    except Exception as e:
        print(f" Failed CalculateSignedKME() on cluster {g}: {e}")
        continue

    kme_df = getattr(wgcna, 'signedKME', None)
    if kme_df is None or kme_df.empty:
        print(f" signedKME is empty for cluster {g}")
        continue

    kme_df.index.name = 'gene'

    #  geneIds 
    gene_ids = list(kme_df.index)
    gene_to_module = wgcna.getModulesGene(gene_ids)

    from collections import defaultdict
    module_gene_dict = defaultdict(list)

    for gene, module in zip(gene_ids, gene_to_module):
        if isinstance(module, pd.Series):
            module = module.iloc[0]
        module_gene_dict[module].append(gene)    # module_gene_dict = wgcna.getModulesGene()
    kme_df.index.name = 'gene'  # index  gene 

    hub_genes_cluster = {}

    for module, genes in module_gene_dict.items():
        df_mod = kme_df.loc[kme_df.index.intersection(genes)]

        # kME
        kme_cols = [c for c in df_mod.columns if c.startswith('kME')]
        if not kme_cols:
            print(f" No kME columns in signedKME for module {module}")
            continue

        # kME
        kmecol = next((c for c in kme_cols if module in c), kme_cols[0])

        top100 = df_mod.sort_values(by=kmecol, ascending=False).head(100)
        hub_genes_cluster[module] = top100

        # 
        output_path = f"./wgcna_10000_{g}/hub_genes_top100_{module}.csv"
        top100.to_csv(output_path)
        print(f" Cluster {g}, module {module}: hub genes saved ({len(top100)})  {output_path}")

cluster_gene_sets = {}

for cluster, modules_dict in hub_genes_all.items():
    combined_genes = set()
    for module, df_genes in modules_dict.items():
        combined_genes.update(df_genes.index)
    cluster_gene_sets[cluster] = combined_genes

# Jaccard
from itertools import combinations

for c1, c2 in combinations(cluster_gene_sets.keys(), 2):
    genes1 = cluster_gene_sets[c1]
    genes2 = cluster_gene_sets[c2]
    intersection = genes1.intersection(genes2)
    union = genes1.union(genes2)
    jaccard = len(intersection) / len(union) if union else 0
    print(f"Jaccard similarity between cluster {c1} and cluster {c2}: {jaccard:.3f}")

        for mod2, genes_df2 in hub_genes_all[g2].items():
            genes2 = set(genes_df2.index)
            intersection = genes1.intersection(genes2)
            union = genes1.union(genes2)
            jaccard = len(intersection) / len(union) if union else 0
            print(f"  Module {mod1} vs {mod2}: Jaccard similarity = {jaccard:.3f}")
